The paper proposes a self-supervised learning approach for medical imaging analysis, specifically for ultrasound video. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on learning representations from unlabelled data, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of video data also suggests that the paper may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
